<paragraph id="8628475BFFB38500FF13F99EFD3CF87E" blockId="20.[136,1452,1595,2018]" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FF13F99EFEE9F9E6" bold="true" box="[189,294,1632,1658]" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FE88F9A1FE34F9E5" authorityName="Ames" authorityYear="1923" box="[294,507,1631,1657]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerea">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FE88F9A1FE34F9E5" box="[294,507,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Pleurothallis cerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been commonly placed under the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FBE9F99EFB25F9E5" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Schlechter" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1095,1258,1632,1657]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomeriae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FBE9F99EFB25F9E5" box="[1095,1258,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. octomeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FABEF99EFA6BF9E5" authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Richard &amp; Galeotti" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1296,1444,1632,1657]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FABEF99EFA6BF9E5" box="[1296,1444,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, Luer noted differences between the two species, and in 1991 annotated a specimen collected by Endrés from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FF69F956FE8EF95D" box="[199,321,1703,1730]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
as “ 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FED8F956FD4DF95E" authority="(Ames) Luer" authorityName="Luer ex Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[374,642,1704,1730]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cereus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FED8F956FE2BF95D" box="[374,484,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. cereus</emphasis>
(Ames) Luer
</taxonomicName>
”, a combination that he never published. When 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFB38500FB0CF956FAE7F95E" author="Soto Arenas, M. A." box="[1186,1320,1704,1730]" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" pagination="4" refId="ref31776" refString="Soto Arenas, M. A. (2008) Myoxanthus. In: Hagsater, E. &amp; Soto, M. (Eds.) Icones orchidacearum 10 (4). Instituto Chinoin, Mexico City, pp. xxii, t. 1053, 1054." type="book chapter" year="2008">Soto (2008)</bibRefCitation>
revised the taxonomy of the Mexican 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FE12F935FD8AF979" authorityName=", Luer" authorityYear="1992" box="[444,581,1739,1765]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FE12F935FD8AF979" box="[444,581,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Myoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he reduced 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FD73F932FC4CF979" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Schlechter" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[733,899,1740,1765]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomeriae">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FD73F932FC4CF979" box="[733,899,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. octomeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with all its synonyms, to the synonymy of the older 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FF65F90EFEADF895" authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Richard &amp; Galeotti" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[203,354,1776,1801]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FF65F90EFEADF895" box="[203,354,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a name based on material from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FD4BF911FCF1F895" box="[741,830,1775,1801]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. However, he also noted the odd features of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FAE7F90EFA6BF895" authorityName="Ames" authorityYear="1923" box="[1353,1444,1776,1801]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerea">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FAE7F90EFA6BF895" box="[1353,1444,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">P. cerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in leaf size and shape and lip structure. After studying material of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FBA8F8EDFB11F8B1" authorityName="Ames" authorityYear="1923" box="[1030,1246,1811,1837]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerea">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FBA8F8EDFB11F8B1" box="[1030,1246,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Pleurothallis cerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FA86F8EAFA68F8B1" box="[1320,1447,1811,1838]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFB38500FF26F8C9FDE9F8CE" author="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P." box="[136,550,1847,1874]" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" pagination="203 - 214" refId="ref31389" refString="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P. (2017) Additions to the Costa Rican Myoxanthus (Orchidaceae: Pleurothallidinae). Lankesteriana 17: 203 - 214. https: // doi. org / 10.15517 / lank. v 17 i 2.29933" type="journal article" year="2017">Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans (2017)</bibRefCitation>
formally recognized it as a species and transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FB22F8C9FADAF8CD" authorityName=", Luer" authorityYear="1992" box="[1164,1301,1847,1873]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FB22F8C9FADAF8CD" box="[1164,1301,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Myoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This Central American species is easily distinguished from the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FCF4F8A2FBD2F8E9" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[858,1053,1883,1909]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomerioides">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FCF4F8A2FBD2F8E9" box="[858,1053,1883,1909]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. octomerioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FB85F8A5FB49F8EA" box="[1067,1158,1883,1910]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Mexico</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FB36F8A2FAE5F8E9" authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Richard &amp; Galeotti" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1176,1322,1884,1909]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FB36F8A2FAE5F8E9" box="[1176,1322,1884,1909]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FA96F8A5FA40F8E9" box="[1336,1423,1883,1909]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to Colombia-Venezuela) and 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB38500FE1AF87EFD80F805" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[436,591,1919,1945]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinatus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FE1AF87EFD80F805" box="[436,591,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">M. pulvinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FDF3F87EFD5DF806" box="[605,658,1920,1946]" name="Peru" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB38500FD64F881FCDFF806" box="[714,784,1919,1946]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) by its broad, elliptic to ovate petiolate leaves, and oblong, conspicuously adaxially verrucose, frequently apiculate lip 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB38500FC84F85AFC8EF821" box="[810,833,1956,1981]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="231">vs</emphasis>
. narrow elliptic, sessile leaves and lip not apiculate of the other species (
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFB38500FEFFF839FD28F87E" author="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P." box="[337,743,1991,2018]" pageId="20" pageNumber="231" pagination="203 - 214" refId="ref31389" refString="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P. (2017) Additions to the Costa Rican Myoxanthus (Orchidaceae: Pleurothallidinae). Lankesteriana 17: 203 - 214. https: // doi. org / 10.15517 / lank. v 17 i 2.29933" type="journal article" year="2017">Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
